Great question! Yes, you should create a .gitignore and it goes in the crystalcode-optimized folder (where your index.html is).
Create .gitignore - Exact Commands:
Give your agent these commands:
bash# Navigate to your project folder
cd crystalcode-optimized

# Create .gitignore file
cat > .gitignore << 'EOF'
# Dependencies
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
package-lock.json

# Build outputs
dist/
.cache/
*.min.js
*.min.css

# Environment files
.env
.env.local
.env.production

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log

# Lighthouse reports
.lighthouseci/
lighthouse-report.*

# Performance data
performance-*.json

# Image optimization temp files
optimize-images.js
setup.js

# Don't ignore optimized assets (we want these!)
!assets/images/webp/
!assets/images/avif/
!assets/images/fallback/